INSTRUCTIONS TO THE AUTHORS

Authors should submit to Programme Chairperson  the original paper and three  
copies,  written  in  English  or in  Portuguese (in the last case the paper 
should  have  and abstract in English),  in A4 size sheets, in single column 
with 3.0 cm  lateral  margins,  3.5 cm top  margin and 2.0 cm bottom margin,
printed preferentially in a laser printer. A submission should be limited to 
10 pages. The fist page should include the  title of the paper, names of the 
authors,  filiation  and  addresses,  followed  by  the  abstract (papers in 
Portuguese  should   contain  English  and  Portuguese  abstracts).  In  the 
proceedings  the  originals  could  be  reduced  70%.  The  pages  should be 
enumerated at back by free hand. The papers should be followed by  a  letter 
with the title of the paper, area, names of the authors, name of the speaker, 
e-mail and normal addresses. The papers will be analyzed  by  the  clearness  
and accurancy of ideas, originality and importance from  results and quality 
of the presentation. The authors should  observe  that  the  article  should 
not be submitted to another conference or magazine.


